\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Photosynthesis is functionally the reverse of respiration; carbon dioxide and water are combined to form the larger molecules of carbohydrate, with the addition of energy from sunlight. Water is absorbed through plant roots, and co2 diffuses into leave through the stomates ( valved poers in the leaf and stem surfaces). }
