\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Termites can be accurately escribed as \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8216\'91tiny social cockaroaches\u8217\'92. Close genetic relationship to wood eating cockaroaches.}
\par\plain \f1\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Human and termites - mutual vulnerability to heat and desiccation.  Neither could survive without sociality. Both live in complex societies. Shared social behaviors enable both humans and termites to constuct complex structuers that protect from extremes of desert climate. }
\par\plain \f1\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Entemologists reserve the name \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8216\'91bug\u8217\'92 for those in the order Hemiptera.  Largest order of insects that undergo incomplete metamorphosis. United by piercing sucking mouthparts. }
