\par\plain \f1\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Cochineal bugs feed on cactus. You may have noticed a white, moldy-looking material growing on the prickly pear cacti in your yard. Beneath this fluffy white mass resides the small cochineal bugs.  Females look like tiny grapes. = smoosh to make red dye.  Hairy red grape dessicated. Shriveled. }
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Body contains a substance called carminic acid. }
\par\plain \f1\fs24\b0\i0
